    "REASON : The proposed extension is considered to be harmful to the character and appearance of the host building and the conservation area.  The extension is an unsensitive addition and disruption to the host building and wider development pattern of the terrace.  The proposal in this regard is considered to be unacceptable and fail to comply with PPS5 Planning and the Historic Environment; policies 7.4, 7.6 and 7.8 of the London Plan 2011, policy CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011; the objectives of policies D4 (Designing in Context), D11 (Extensions and Alterations) and D28 (Rear Extensions) of the Islington Unitary Development Plan, part 2.5 of the Islington Urban Design Guide, and the guidance of the East Canonbury Conservation Area Design Guidelines."
